Dear camlers,

I modified ocamllex. It can produce now functorized lexers (over
tokens and possibly another module), which may share some common
signatures etc. I needed these kind of features for a software with
seven parsers, whose maintenance was a nightmare.

I would like now to modify the master LaTeX document from which are
automatically produced the different kinds of OCaml docs (HTML, PDF
etc.), then my work may be useful to others. 

Do someone know where this document and the suitable Makefile are?

Is there an other way to proceed?

Best regards,

-- 

Christian

PS By the way, functorized parsers over tokens would be very useful
too. Did someone bootstraped the front-end of ocamlyacc (ie not the
parser engine)?

